Day 41: Write a Docker File

Date: October 6, 2025
Overview
Created my first Dockerfile for automated image building.
Key Concepts Learned

Dockerfile syntax
Build instructions (FROM, RUN, COPY, CMD, ENTRYPOINT)
Layer caching
Multi-stage builds

Commands Used
dockerfileFROM ubuntu:20.04
RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y nginx
COPY . /var/www/html
EXPOSE 80
CMD ["nginx", "-g", "daemon off;"]
bashdocker build -t my-image:v1 .
Challenges Faced
Layer caching and optimization! Learned to order commands properly to leverage cache effectively.
